<subSubSection lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="118" pageId="30" pageNumber="117" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[676,1211,1515,1700]" box="[677,821,1515,1541]" pageId="30" pageNumber="117">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[676,1211,1515,1700]" lastBlockId="31.[111,646,216,306]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="118" pageId="30" pageNumber="117">
Disc-like body, brown-colored, with radially arranged cell rows; the margins of the body are thin and irregular. The “ostiole” is not distinct, but a hole in the center of the disc is present, formed by dissolving of the central cells. Cells are square to elongated, without pore, 
<quantity box="[377,468,216,243]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="31" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="3.0">3-10 µm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[571,646,216,243]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="31" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 µm</quantity>
wide. Cells of the central part of the disc are thicker. Equatorial diameter = 
<quantity box="[354,466,279,306]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.75" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.5" pageId="31" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="67.5" valueMax="70.0" valueMin="65.0">65-70 µm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[113,646,343,433]" box="[113,352,343,369]" pageId="31" pageNumber="118">BOTANICAL AFFINITIES</paragraph>
